\begin{proof}
Assume $H_n>h$, so there exists a vertex $v$ at generation $h + 1$. Let $u$ be its ancestor at generation $h-(s-1)$. Since the mass decreases by at most one at each step, we have $K(v) \ge K(u) - s$. Since $K(v) \ge 1$, this implies $K(u) \le s+1$, which proves the inclusion.
\end{proof}

