By Lemma~\ref{lem:Mixed}, $\mathbb E[C_j] = \frac{\theta}{j} R_{m,j}(\theta)$. Since $R_{m,j}(\theta)$ is the ratio of Gamma functions, and $\Gamma(x)$ is increasing for $x > 2$, it follows that $R_{m,j}(\theta) \le 1$ for all $j$. Thus $\mathbb E[\widetilde N_0] \le \theta \sum_{j \in J} \frac{1}{j}$. This sum converges to a constant as $m \to \infty$, so $\widetilde N_0$ is bounded in probability.
